about.description:
castorapi is a python API wrapper for the Castor EDC API to
fetch data from your clinical study.
The author is not affiliated with Castor EDC. Use at your own risk.
about.summary: Python API wrapper for Castor EDC to fetch data from you clinical study.

name: castorapi
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "castorapi" %}
{% set version = "0.1" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: "https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  sha256: 4544ab11e1144c1a66a466f5ffc379ff1031babe6d74c0fba027f3d4fd6d3b0c

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - json5
    - pandas
    - pip
    - progressbar2
    - python
    - requests
  run:
    - json5
    - pandas
    - progressbar2
    - python
    - requests

test:
  imports:
    - castorapi

about:
  home: "https://github.com/wouterpotters/castorapi"
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: "LICENSE"
  summary: "Python API wrapper for Castor EDC to fetch data from you clinical study."
  doc_url: "https://github.com/wouterpotters/castorapi#usage"
  dev_url: "https://github.com/wouterpotters/castorapi"
  description: |
    castorapi is a python API wrapper for the Castor EDC API to 
    fetch data from your clinical study.
    The author is not affiliated with Castor EDC. Use at your own risk.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - wouterpotters
